        <p>
            The Garud Commando Force is the special forces unit of the Indian Air Force. It was formed in September 2004
            and has a current strength of over 1500 personnel. The unit derives its name from Garuda, a divine bird-like
            creature in Indian history.
        </p>
        <p>
            Garud is tasked with the protection of critical Air Force bases and installations; search and rescue during
            peace and hostilities and disaster relief during calamities. Presently, Garuds are deployed in Congo as part
            of the UN peace keeping operations.
        </p>
        <p>
            It was formed in September , 2004 , after an attack on air bases in J&K.
        </p>
        <p>
            Originally named as “Tiger Force” but later it was changed to “Garud Commando Force”
        </p>
        <p>
        <h4><u> Insignia</u></h4>
        <ul style="color: maroon;">
            <li>Maroon Beret</li>
            <li>Garud Commando Force Patch</li>
            <li>Garud Logo</li>
        </ul>
        </p><br>
