        <p><b><u>Vir Chakra</u></b>-Vir Chakra is an Indian gallantry award presented for acts of bravery on the battlefield inducted on 26 th Jan 1950. It replaced the British Distinguished Service Cross (DSC), Military Cross (MC) and Distinguished Flying Cross (DFC). The recipient uses “ Vr.C.” as a post-nominal abbreviation</p>
